OL,3,CResidents 'deeply concerned' at plans
OL,4,Cto house child asylum seekers in care
OL,5,Chome
OL,7,FPeople on the Isle of Sheppey have
OL,8,Fexpressed their anger over plans to
OL,9,Fhouse unaccompanied asylum seeking
OL,10,Fchildren in a care home in Minster-on-
OL,11,FSea.
OL,13,FKent County Council is proposing to
OL,14,Fhouse 50 children aged 16 and 17, at
OL,15,Fthe empty Ocean Heights Residential
OL,16,FCare Home in Seaside Avenue.
OL,18,FIn a letter sent to residents, the
OL,19,Fcouncil say the site is due to open
OL,20,Fnext month.
